org.safs.selenium.webdriver.lib.model

Class EmbeddedObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.safs.selenium.webdriver.lib.model.EmbeddedObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Supportable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractSelectable, CheckBox.AbstractCheckable, ComboBox.HtmlSelect, ScrollBar.AbstractScrollable

    public abstract class EmbeddedObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements Supportable
    This class represents an object to be included in the org.safs.selenium.webdriver.lib.Component
    or its subclass. This class provides an ability to detect whether the webelement is supported for
    a certain Component (Tree, ListView) whatever the domain (DOJO, SAP, HTML) this webelement belongs to.
    Subclass needs to provide the method Supportable.getSupportedClassNames().

    Author:
    Lei Wang APR 25, 2014 Initial release.

      • refresh

        public boolean refresh(boolean checkStale)
        If some native javascript APIs are called, the parent's under-lying web element may become stale.
        In this case, this refresh() method needs to be called.
        Normally before calling webelement() to get a webelement, you may call this refresh(boolean).
        Parameters:
        checkStale - boolean, if true then check if the element is stale or not before refresh; ohterwise, then refresh the element directly. The check will spend some time, if you don't want to waste time, use false.
        Returns:
        boolean, true if the refresh succeed
        See Also:
        webelement()

      • isShowOnPage

        protected boolean isShowOnPage(Element element)
                        throws SeleniumPlusException
        To check if an Element is visible on page. This method will check:
        • If the element is considered as visible by Selenium
        • If the center of the element is in the container
        • If the item is shown in browser
        Parameters:
        element - Element, the element to check
        Returns:
        boolean, true if the element is visible on page.
        Throws:
        SeleniumPlusException
